==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sillabub
<hw>Sil"la*bub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<ets>sile</ets> to strain, and <ets>bub</ets> liquor, also Prov. E.
<ets>sillibauk</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dish made by mixing wine or cider
with milk, and thus forming a soft curd; also, sweetened cream, flavored
with wine and beaten to a stiff froth.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>syllabub</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siller</ent>⟦br⟧
